  "time_ut": 1656914524,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d87\u0db8\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dcf\u0da5\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0dc3\u0dd6\u0da0\u0dd2 \u0db6\u0dd0\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A poop bank from American scientists",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "If all goes the way scientists hope, putting your dead on ice for use at some point in life could become the norm.",
        "A group of scientists researching the physiological and psychological functioning of the alimentary system has wanted to set up a bank to deposit dead samples, just as umbilical cord blood samples are deposited in a blood bank.",
        "A transplant of beneficial bacteria found in feces into the intestine has an advantage over an umbilical cord blood transplant, scientists said, because it increases the function of the digestive system. This transplant is called FMT.",
        "Umbilical cord blood, rich in primordial cells, can be used to treat certain cancers, immune system deficiencies and certain genetic disorders, but transplanting the beneficial bacteria found in the feces into the gut can also be used to treat asthma, diabetes and a neurological condition called MS, which affects the brain and spinal cord. Scientists hope to be able to use it in the future.",
        "Also, researchers believe that transplanting the beneficial bacteria found in feces may lead to future treatments for obesity and delaying aging.",
        "A group of scientists led by Dr. Yang Yu Ling of Harvard Medical School has made this proposal. FMT is already used to treat bacterial infections of the digestive system.",
        "The transplant is usually done through a tube inserted directly into the stomach through the nose. But the bacteria can be implanted directly into the colon through surgery or a pill.",
        "Only faecal samples from a person who has undergone numerous health tests to ensure that there is no disease and has been certified healthy are taken for transplantation.",
        "A British donor can get \u00a310 (about Rs. 4500) for a sample and an American can get US$50 (about Rs. 18,000)."
      ],
